As the Tshwane Municipality ramps up its debt collection campaign, some of the attention has been turned to housing estates and complexes - which collectively owe hundreds of millions in outstanding rates and utility bills. Barry Bateman has more #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - In the two weeks since the start of the debt collection campaign, the Tshwane municipality has recovered R500 million of the R17-billion owed to them. The initial focus was on government departments and businesses. However, now, the attention has shifted to the suburbs. Some of the big consumers disconnected have been estates and complexes. READ: Tshwane to continue cutting power for defaulters In other instances, it is the bodies corporate and homeowners associations at fault as they are not paying the collected funds over to the municipality. That is where the Community Schemes Ombud Service can step in. They receive over about 8000 complaints a year. The City Tshwane has vowed to continue its crackdown. Watch the video above for more details on this story.